1
00:01:36,496 --> 00:01:37,464
Excuse me. Coming through.

2
00:01:37,764 --> 00:01:38,531
Please make way.

3
00:01:38,731 --> 00:01:39,132
You two.

4
00:01:40,233 --> 00:01:40,834
What are you doing here?

5
00:01:41,000 --> 00:01:42,068
Director Lin doesn't take walk-ins.

6
00:01:42,135 --> 00:01:42,936
I know, I know.

7
00:01:42,936 --> 00:01:44,304
I just need to say a few words to him.

8
00:01:44,571 --> 00:01:45,038
You can't go in.

9
00:01:45,038 --> 00:01:45,472
Sorry.

10
00:01:45,638 --> 00:01:46,172
What number are you?

11
00:01:46,239 --> 00:01:46,773
Excuse me.

12
00:01:47,373 --> 00:01:48,441
Why won't you listen?

13
00:01:48,441 --> 00:01:49,509
I just need a few words.

14
00:01:49,576 --> 00:01:50,610
Just a few words.

15
00:01:50,810 --> 00:01:51,277
What's going on?

16
00:01:51,277 --> 00:01:52,645
Director Lin, they forced their way in.

17
00:01:52,712 --> 00:01:53,346
Director Lin.

18
00:01:53,413 --> 00:01:55,014
Please add us to the list.

19
00:01:55,515 --> 00:01:57,050
I couldn't book you online.

20
00:01:57,050 --> 00:01:58,551
And I couldn't register on-site either.

21
00:01:59,052 --> 00:02:00,253
Director Lin doesn't add extra patients.

22
00:02:00,253 --> 00:02:00,520
You...

23
00:02:03,556 --> 00:02:04,390
What's wrong with the gentleman?

24
00:02:04,691 --> 00:02:05,358
Coronary heart disease.

25
00:02:05,892 --> 00:02:07,227
He had angiography at another hospital.

26
00:02:07,393 --> 00:02:08,361
I have the report here.

27
00:02:08,561 --> 00:02:09,462
What did their doctors say?

28
00:02:09,596 --> 00:02:11,064
They said one vessel

29
00:02:11,064 --> 00:02:11,865
is completely blocked,

30
00:02:12,031 --> 00:02:12,932
and several others

31
00:02:12,999 --> 00:02:14,434
are severely narrowed.

32
00:02:15,835 --> 00:02:16,669
How many are still waiting?

33
00:02:17,103 --> 00:02:17,971
More than thirty.

34
00:02:18,171 --> 00:02:18,905
The list is full.

35
00:02:19,839 --> 00:02:21,107
Please help us.

36
00:02:21,241 --> 00:02:22,308
Look at him.

37
00:02:22,308 --> 00:02:23,676
He can't eat or sleep.

38
00:02:23,810 --> 00:02:24,878
He's suffering terribly.

39
00:02:24,944 --> 00:02:25,678
And the other hospital

40
00:02:25,712 --> 00:02:26,813
couldn't treat him either.

41
00:02:27,413 --> 00:02:27,881
Director Lin.

42
00:02:28,014 --> 00:02:29,115
I've read reports

43
00:02:29,115 --> 00:02:29,816
about you.

44
00:02:29,816 --> 00:02:30,350
They say you're exceptionally skilled.

45
00:02:30,350 --> 00:02:31,050
All right, all right.

46
00:02:31,951 --> 00:02:32,719
I'll add you,

47
00:02:32,785 --> 00:02:33,586
but you'll be last.

48
00:02:33,720 --> 00:02:34,320
You'll need to wait.

49
00:02:35,321 --> 00:02:36,823
Okay. Thank you so much.

50
00:02:36,890 --> 00:02:37,490
Wait outside, please.

51
00:02:37,490 --> 00:02:37,957
Thank you. Thank you.

52
00:02:37,957 --> 00:02:38,625
Hurry. Come on.

53
00:02:38,691 --> 00:02:40,393
Sorry. Sorry.

54
00:02:41,161 --> 00:02:41,561
Have a seat.

55
00:02:42,762 --> 00:02:43,329
Sorry.

56
00:02:46,633 --> 00:02:47,367
Are you okay?

57
00:02:48,168 --> 00:02:48,801
How are you feeling?

58
00:02:53,773 --> 00:02:55,108
That was the last one, right?

59
00:02:55,241 --> 00:02:55,575
Yes.

60
00:02:56,142 --> 00:02:56,709
Director, you need to hurry

61
00:02:56,709 --> 00:02:57,610
to the airport, don't you?

62
00:02:58,478 --> 00:02:59,546
Yes. I'm running late.

63
00:03:03,650 --> 00:03:04,250
Wait, Director.

64
00:03:05,118 --> 00:03:05,952
There's one more.

65
00:03:06,653 --> 00:03:07,754
The one you just added.

66
00:03:12,125 --> 00:03:12,959
All right. Send them in.

67
00:03:13,026 --> 00:03:13,326
Okay.

68
00:03:15,628 --> 00:03:15,929
Hello.

69
00:03:16,229 --> 00:03:16,763
Take it slowly.

70
00:03:17,664 --> 00:03:18,331
Director Lin.

71
00:03:18,965 --> 00:03:19,566
Sorry to keep you waiting.

72
00:03:20,200 --> 00:03:20,600
Please.

73
00:03:23,570 --> 00:03:24,003
Director Lin,

74
00:03:24,304 --> 00:03:25,572
this is the angiography report

75
00:03:25,638 --> 00:03:27,574
from the other hospital.

76
00:03:27,574 --> 00:03:28,174
Please take a look.

77
00:03:29,475 --> 00:03:30,343
No images?

78
00:03:30,710 --> 00:03:31,144
They're here.

79
00:03:31,344 --> 00:03:33,012
I saved them on the camera.

80
00:03:33,880 --> 00:03:34,447
One moment.

81
00:03:35,014 --> 00:03:35,682
Here it is.

82
00:03:35,815 --> 00:03:36,649
Please look.

83
00:03:43,423 --> 00:03:45,425
He also has hypertension,

84
00:03:45,558 --> 00:03:46,359
diabetes,

85
00:03:46,526 --> 00:03:48,161
and several other chronic illnesses.

86
00:03:48,361 --> 00:03:49,329
I wrote them all down here.

87
00:03:49,529 --> 00:03:50,330
Please take a look.

88
00:03:53,533 --> 00:03:54,133
I don't need that.

89
00:03:58,371 --> 00:03:59,706
From the images,

90
00:04:01,507 --> 00:04:02,442
your father's coronary arteries

91
00:04:02,442 --> 00:04:03,276
are severely blocked.

92
00:04:04,844 --> 00:04:05,812
I'm his wife.

93
00:04:14,187 --> 00:04:14,787
Hold onto this.

94
00:04:17,423 --> 00:04:18,491
For someone in his condition,

95
00:04:18,691 --> 00:04:19,826
my recommendation

96
00:04:20,627 --> 00:04:21,527
is a median sternotomy.

97
00:04:23,062 --> 00:04:24,364
Could it be done thoracoscopically?

98
00:04:24,530 --> 00:04:25,531
I heard that's possible,

99
00:04:25,565 --> 00:04:26,833
without cardiopulmonary bypass,

100
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:28,468
with the heart still beating.

101
00:04:30,236 --> 00:04:31,437
Thoracoscopy is possible,

102
00:04:31,971 --> 00:04:33,206
but his lung function is poor,

103
00:04:33,506 --> 00:04:34,274
so he isn't a good candidate.

104
00:04:38,144 --> 00:04:38,678
I see.

105
00:04:38,845 --> 00:04:39,846
I've reviewed

106
00:04:39,846 --> 00:04:41,481
some related literature.

107
00:04:41,648 --> 00:04:42,949
It says coronary disease

108
00:04:43,116 --> 00:04:44,651
is closely linked

109
00:04:44,651 --> 00:04:45,752
to lifestyle habits.

110
00:04:45,952 --> 00:04:46,886
For example,

111
00:04:46,919 --> 00:04:48,087
smoking and drinking...

112
00:04:48,288 --> 00:04:49,889
But he never smokes or drinks.

113
00:04:49,889 --> 00:04:51,391
He doesn't have those habits.

114
00:04:51,824 --> 00:04:52,925
The mechanism is complicated.

115
00:04:52,992 --> 00:04:53,726
No one can say for sure.

116
00:04:53,993 --> 00:04:54,827
And discussing that now

117
00:04:54,827 --> 00:04:55,695
doesn't help.

118
00:04:56,162 --> 00:04:57,130
The issue is treatment.

119
00:04:59,265 --> 00:05:01,034
Knowing what happens but not why

120
00:05:01,034 --> 00:05:01,601
isn't exactly

121
00:05:01,634 --> 00:05:02,835
a scientific approach.

122
00:05:03,169 --> 00:05:04,270
I've documented

123
00:05:04,304 --> 00:05:05,438
our daily habits

124
00:05:05,571 --> 00:05:06,105
and other characteristics

125
00:05:06,105 --> 00:05:07,206
in the appendix.

126
00:05:07,373 --> 00:05:08,274
You can take a look.

127
00:05:08,508 --> 00:05:10,043
Maybe it could inspire

128
00:05:10,176 --> 00:05:10,743
Listen to me.

129
00:05:10,743 --> 00:05:11,411
your medical recommendation.

130
00:05:11,411 --> 00:05:12,045
Listen to me.

131
00:05:12,045 --> 00:05:13,012
Wouldn't it be useful?

132
00:05:16,916 --> 00:05:18,051
My medical opinion,

133
00:05:18,184 --> 00:05:19,385
given his condition,

134
00:05:20,386 --> 00:05:21,688
is a median sternotomy.

135
00:05:22,055 --> 00:05:23,523
But he's elderly,

136
00:05:23,589 --> 00:05:25,091
and his overall condition is poor.

137
00:05:25,324 --> 00:05:27,026
We can't guarantee postoperative recovery.

138
00:05:28,394 --> 00:05:29,762
Are you in a hurry?

139
00:05:31,331 --> 00:05:32,865
I waited outside for you

140
00:05:32,932 --> 00:05:34,233
for four full hours,

141
00:05:34,567 --> 00:05:36,302
and you won't give me four minutes?

142
00:05:36,602 --> 00:05:37,637
We're discussing treatment.

143
00:05:37,904 --> 00:05:39,305
Length isn't the issue.

144
00:05:40,106 --> 00:05:41,307
You asked for my surgical opinion.

145
00:05:41,407 --> 00:05:42,241
I've given it.

146
00:05:42,408 --> 00:05:43,276
You may accept it

147
00:05:43,376 --> 00:05:44,210
or reject it.

148
00:05:44,277 --> 00:05:45,445
You can go home and discuss it,

149
00:05:45,478 --> 00:05:46,713
or if you have other ideas,

150
00:05:46,879 --> 00:05:47,747
you can ask Cardiology

151
00:05:47,747 --> 00:05:48,214
about an intervention.

152
00:05:49,282 --> 00:05:51,284
Of course we've considered that,

153
00:05:51,651 --> 00:05:52,919
but the lower-level hospital said

154
00:05:53,152 --> 00:05:55,188
it would be very difficult too.

155
00:05:57,357 --> 00:05:57,690
How about this?

156
00:05:59,025 --> 00:05:59,992
Go see

157
00:05:59,992 --> 00:06:01,227
Director Zhou Xiaofeng in Cardiology.

158
00:06:01,294 --> 00:06:02,228
Ask him to think of a solution.

159
00:06:02,562 --> 00:06:04,063
I'll give him a heads-up, all right?

160
00:06:09,836 --> 00:06:10,503
There's nothing we can do.

161
00:06:10,603 --> 00:06:11,671
Cardiology has

162
00:06:11,671 --> 00:06:12,605
so many chronic and elderly patients.

163
00:06:12,605 --> 00:06:13,706
Far too many.

164
00:06:13,806 --> 00:06:15,274
And the elderly are stubborn.

165
00:06:15,908 --> 00:06:17,210
They refuse to take medication properly.

166
00:06:17,610 --> 00:06:19,011
When I recommend a stent,

167
00:06:19,078 --> 00:06:19,645
they act as if I'm trying

168
00:06:19,645 --> 00:06:20,613
to rob and kill them.

169
00:06:20,813 --> 00:06:21,347
They won't even be discharged.

170
00:06:21,347 --> 00:06:21,881
Director Zhou.

171
00:06:21,881 --> 00:06:22,248
I...

172
00:06:22,915 --> 00:06:24,884
Are you Director Zhou from Cardiology?

173
00:06:25,351 --> 00:06:26,386
Director Zhou Xiaofeng?

174
00:06:26,652 --> 00:06:27,053
Yes.

175
00:06:27,653 --> 00:06:28,488
Hello. Hello.

176
00:06:29,122 --> 00:06:30,156
Director Lin from Cardiac Surgery

177
00:06:30,156 --> 00:06:31,157
asked us to see you.

178
00:06:31,491 --> 00:06:32,391
Director Lin Yi.

179
00:06:32,558 --> 00:06:33,159
Yes, yes.

180
00:06:33,426 --> 00:06:34,627
Can our case be treated?

181
00:06:34,627 --> 00:06:35,695
Can surgery be done?

182
00:06:39,332 --> 00:06:39,866
Sorry.

183
00:06:39,932 --> 00:06:40,800
I don't know the details yet.

184
00:06:41,734 --> 00:06:43,403
Didn't he call you?

185
00:06:46,305 --> 00:06:48,708
Maybe reception was bad in the clinic.

186
00:06:50,042 --> 00:06:51,210
He clearly said

187
00:06:51,210 --> 00:06:52,812
he'd call you right away.

188
00:06:53,079 --> 00:06:54,413
What kind of attitude is that?

189
00:06:54,447 --> 00:06:55,615
Terrible medical ethics.

190
00:06:55,648 --> 00:06:56,649
Please don't get upset.

191
00:06:57,150 --> 00:06:58,384
Tell me what happened, slowly.

192
00:06:58,484 --> 00:06:58,885
All right?

193
00:07:01,988 --> 00:07:02,488
Okay.

194
00:07:06,025 --> 00:07:06,492
Indeed,

195
00:07:07,293 --> 00:07:08,928
the occluded segment is long,

196
00:07:09,095 --> 00:07:10,596
and the calcification is severe.

197
00:07:11,330 --> 00:07:12,432
An intervention

198
00:07:12,598 --> 00:07:13,766
would be technically difficult.

199
00:07:14,967 --> 00:07:16,436
Can it still be done?

200
00:07:17,270 --> 00:07:18,638
He's seventy-eight.

201
00:07:19,172 --> 00:07:20,406
The risk is high.

202
00:07:22,642 --> 00:07:24,710
What happens

203
00:07:25,111 --> 00:07:26,279
if the procedure fails?

204
00:07:26,879 --> 00:07:28,681
In severe cases, the vessel may rupture.

205
00:07:29,282 --> 00:07:30,650
If that happens,

206
00:07:30,716 --> 00:07:32,051
Cardiac Surgery would need

207
00:07:32,151 --> 00:07:33,252
to open the chest and repair it.

208
00:07:36,722 --> 00:07:38,324
What is the approximate

209
00:07:38,357 --> 00:07:39,225
success rate?

210
00:07:39,992 --> 00:07:40,960
I can't give you

211
00:07:40,960 --> 00:07:42,195
an exact number.

212
00:07:42,628 --> 00:07:43,930
Every patient is different.

213
00:07:44,397 --> 00:07:45,264
We can only explain the risks

214
00:07:45,364 --> 00:07:46,199
in advance.

215
00:07:52,605 --> 00:07:52,905
Hello?

216
00:07:55,007 --> 00:07:56,108
I know. I'm coming now.

217
00:07:57,210 --> 00:07:57,677
I'm sorry.

218
00:07:57,710 --> 00:07:59,011
I need to return to the ward.

219
00:07:59,478 --> 00:08:01,247
Think it over carefully.

220
00:08:01,314 --> 00:08:02,448
If you decide on the procedure,

221
00:08:02,448 --> 00:08:03,349
come back to me.

222
00:08:04,116 --> 00:08:06,319
Okay. We'll discuss it.

223
00:08:11,557 --> 00:08:13,192
With such severe disease,

224
00:08:13,526 --> 00:08:14,193
we could consider

225
00:08:14,193 --> 00:08:15,294
an intravascular lithotripsy balloon.

226
00:08:15,528 --> 00:08:16,696
The result should be good.

227
00:08:17,530 --> 00:08:18,865
We'll follow your recommendation.

228
00:08:20,233 --> 00:08:20,666
Director,

229
00:08:21,033 --> 00:08:22,201
can my father

230
00:08:22,201 --> 00:08:22,969
be admitted today?

231
00:08:23,502 --> 00:08:24,704
We need to check for a bed first.

232
00:08:25,071 --> 00:08:25,638
Zhang Zhen.

233
00:08:33,045 --> 00:08:33,846
I'll check now.

234
00:08:35,815 --> 00:08:37,049
I'll notify you once I know.

235
00:08:37,483 --> 00:08:38,050
Thank you.

236
00:08:50,129 --> 00:08:50,630
From now on,

237
00:08:52,465 --> 00:08:53,432
the Director is counting on you.

238
00:08:55,001 --> 00:08:56,369
He likes coffee.

239
00:08:57,136 --> 00:08:58,004
Sometimes, with his second

240
00:08:58,037 --> 00:08:58,905
or third cup,

241
00:08:59,639 --> 00:09:00,306
quietly swap it

242
00:09:00,373 --> 00:09:01,307
for decaf.

243
00:09:02,441 --> 00:09:03,442
Every so often,

244
00:09:03,509 --> 00:09:04,877
check the cabinet stock.

245
00:09:05,611 --> 00:09:06,112
Don't let it run out.

246
00:09:07,480 --> 00:09:09,548
The department secretary is careless

247
00:09:10,283 --> 00:09:10,950
and often forgets.

248
00:09:17,023 --> 00:09:17,957
When other departments request

249
00:09:17,957 --> 00:09:18,624
multidisciplinary consultations,

250
00:09:18,824 --> 00:09:20,326
he always goes whenever called.

251
00:09:20,893 --> 00:09:22,094
You need to stop him sometimes.

252
00:09:23,930 --> 00:09:25,064
If they don't specifically need him,

253
00:09:25,231 --> 00:09:26,465
ask another director to go.

254
00:09:26,999 --> 00:09:28,134
And don't let too many

255
00:09:28,167 --> 00:09:28,968
extra patients into his clinic.

256
00:09:29,402 --> 00:09:30,069
He's soft-hearted.

257
00:09:30,703 --> 00:09:32,071
The moment patients or families plead,

258
00:09:32,104 --> 00:09:32,872
he adds them.

259
00:09:34,073 --> 00:09:35,107
Sometimes he's so busy

260
00:09:35,308 --> 00:09:36,175
he misses lunch.

261
00:09:37,310 --> 00:09:38,077
So you can

262
00:09:38,110 --> 00:09:38,744
buy him something to eat.

263
00:09:39,045 --> 00:09:40,146
But he doesn't like sweets.

264
00:09:41,113 --> 00:09:41,914
I'll remember.

265
00:09:42,515 --> 00:09:43,783
I'll order light meals for him.

266
00:09:45,351 --> 00:09:46,252
In the whole hospital,

267
00:09:47,987 --> 00:09:49,455
Dr. Fang and Director Lin

268
00:09:49,555 --> 00:09:50,523
can persuade him best.

269
00:09:52,024 --> 00:09:52,925
If necessary,

270
00:09:53,225 --> 00:09:54,560
ask them for help.

271
00:09:55,227 --> 00:09:55,728
Understand?

272
00:10:00,533 --> 00:10:00,967
Sisi.

273
00:10:04,203 --> 00:10:04,837
Work hard.

274
00:10:08,474 --> 00:10:09,241
Don't end up like me.

275
00:10:22,722 --> 00:10:23,289
Take care.

276
00:10:34,867 --> 00:10:35,601
In his case,

277
00:10:35,601 --> 00:10:36,836
medication is still acceptable.

278
00:10:36,869 --> 00:10:38,037
We can continue observing.

279
00:10:38,270 --> 00:10:39,438
I'll prescribe another week.

280
00:10:40,239 --> 00:10:40,673
Director.

281
00:10:41,640 --> 00:10:42,308
I checked.

282
00:10:42,508 --> 00:10:43,376
We only have

283
00:10:43,409 --> 00:10:44,076
one bed left.

284
00:10:45,077 --> 00:10:45,911
Isn't that perfect?

285
00:10:46,612 --> 00:10:47,680
But this morning,

286
00:10:47,680 --> 00:10:49,048
after your clinic ended,

287
00:10:49,215 --> 00:10:50,049
didn't you also accept

288
00:10:50,049 --> 00:10:51,384
an elderly man with triple-vessel disease?

289
00:10:52,385 --> 00:10:53,119
Mr. Peng.

290
00:10:53,753 --> 00:10:54,086
Yes.

291
00:10:54,553 --> 00:10:56,055
His family just came to ask.

292
00:10:56,255 --> 00:10:57,256
They want admission too.

293
00:10:57,923 --> 00:10:58,991
Have they decided on surgery?

294
00:11:00,993 --> 00:11:02,495
The lady kept asking me

295
00:11:02,561 --> 00:11:04,196
the same questions over and over,

296
00:11:04,663 --> 00:11:06,198
but still hasn't decided.

297
00:11:08,034 --> 00:11:09,335
Give them more time.

298
00:11:09,668 --> 00:11:10,603
Admit the patient

299
00:11:10,603 --> 00:11:11,003
we just saw first.

300
00:11:11,303 --> 00:11:11,671
Okay.

301
00:11:13,572 --> 00:11:13,973
Xiao Ye.

302
00:11:17,143 --> 00:11:17,843
Go find

303
00:11:17,877 --> 00:11:18,644
Mr. Peng and his family again.

304
00:11:18,844 --> 00:11:19,812
Recommend Cardiac Surgery.

305
00:11:20,346 --> 00:11:21,147
Given his condition,

306
00:11:21,414 --> 00:11:22,548
surgery is more appropriate.

307
00:11:23,249 --> 00:11:23,616
Okay.

308
00:11:25,251 --> 00:11:26,085
Does this work for you?

309
00:11:26,285 --> 00:11:26,686
Yes.

310
00:11:27,053 --> 00:11:27,453
Good.

311
00:11:29,688 --> 00:11:30,189
Director.

312
00:11:31,190 --> 00:11:32,591
Have you eaten lunch?

313
00:11:36,328 --> 00:11:37,596
All right. I understand.

314
00:11:43,069 --> 00:11:44,270
With Zhang Zhen gone,

315
00:11:44,437 --> 00:11:46,005
Zhou Xiaofeng has lost his right-hand man.

316
00:11:46,472 --> 00:11:47,373
Too careless.

317
00:11:51,410 --> 00:11:52,511
Was it really carelessness?

318
00:11:54,814 --> 00:11:55,748
Director Zhou

319
00:11:55,915 --> 00:11:56,916
will eventually understand

320
00:11:57,349 --> 00:11:58,684
that the younger doctors under him

321
00:11:58,751 --> 00:11:59,685
need to make a living.

322
00:12:00,086 --> 00:12:01,087
If you never give them any meat,

323
00:12:01,187 --> 00:12:02,188
who will fight for you?

324
00:12:04,957 --> 00:12:06,325
But he's pushing back now.

325
00:12:07,159 --> 00:12:07,760
Cardiology recently

326
00:12:07,827 --> 00:12:09,161
ordered a batch of lithotripsy balloons.

327
00:12:09,495 --> 00:12:10,830
They want to use new technology

328
00:12:10,930 --> 00:12:11,730
to open up the market

329
00:12:12,131 --> 00:12:13,165
and attract more patients.

330
00:12:14,133 --> 00:12:14,567
Really?

331
00:12:14,867 --> 00:12:15,334
Yes.

332
00:12:18,304 --> 00:12:19,238
In that case,

333
00:12:19,638 --> 00:12:20,639
this young director

334
00:12:20,806 --> 00:12:22,041
does have drive.

335
00:12:22,575 --> 00:12:24,110
You need real strength to forge iron.

336
00:12:24,343 --> 00:12:25,044
He has ability,

337
00:12:25,211 --> 00:12:25,911
and even more courage.

338
00:12:28,347 --> 00:12:28,814
All right.

339
00:12:29,248 --> 00:12:30,116
Same old saying:

340
00:12:30,516 --> 00:12:31,784
when the snipe and clam fight...

341
00:12:33,953 --> 00:12:35,287
I forgot to write the weekly report.

342
00:12:35,554 --> 00:12:36,322
I'll go do it.

343
00:12:40,826 --> 00:12:42,294
the fisherman profits.

344
00:12:55,174 --> 00:12:56,509
Hello. I'm here for admission.

345
00:12:57,009 --> 00:12:58,611
Which director issued the order?

346
00:12:58,878 --> 00:13:00,012
Director Luo from Cardiac Surgery.

347
00:13:00,346 --> 00:13:00,813
All right.

348
00:13:05,451 --> 00:13:06,685
Sir, what's your name?

349
00:13:08,087 --> 00:13:08,554
Peng Mao.

350
00:13:26,839 --> 00:13:27,773
How is everything? All right?

351
00:13:28,574 --> 00:13:29,408
Good. Good.

352
00:13:30,409 --> 00:13:32,478
Look what I made.

353
00:13:37,850 --> 00:13:38,684
Lion's head meatballs.

354
00:13:39,285 --> 00:13:40,486
I never thought I'd get

355
00:13:40,519 --> 00:13:42,121
your specialty while hospitalized.

356
00:13:43,722 --> 00:13:44,523
Have you eaten?

357
00:13:45,090 --> 00:13:46,525
Don't worry. I already did.

358
00:13:52,831 --> 00:13:54,567
You can only have a quarter at lunch.

359
00:13:54,867 --> 00:13:55,668
No more.

360
00:13:56,368 --> 00:13:56,769
All right.

361
00:14:04,343 --> 00:14:05,511
Did the doctor say

362
00:14:05,878 --> 00:14:07,546
how long the surgery will take?

363
00:14:08,147 --> 00:14:09,648
I looked it up online.

364
00:14:10,149 --> 00:14:12,384
Probably over three hours.

365
00:14:13,319 --> 00:14:15,254
Director Luo is so busy

366
00:14:15,354 --> 00:14:16,355
we can never catch him,

367
00:14:16,455 --> 00:14:17,389
so we didn't discuss much.

368
00:14:19,892 --> 00:14:22,094
That Cardiology procedure before

369
00:14:23,195 --> 00:14:24,763
went in through the leg.

370
00:14:25,531 --> 00:14:26,565
Wasn't that better?

371
00:14:28,067 --> 00:14:29,068
Then you wouldn't need

372
00:14:29,635 --> 00:14:30,369
to go through

373
00:14:30,369 --> 00:14:31,770
being cut open.

374
00:14:33,005 --> 00:14:34,273
Old Yang in our building

375
00:14:34,373 --> 00:14:35,441
had heart disease too.

376
00:14:36,742 --> 00:14:38,611
He had an intervention.

377
00:14:39,311 --> 00:14:41,447
Everyone's condition is different.

378
00:14:41,947 --> 00:14:42,882
Director Luo said

379
00:14:43,215 --> 00:14:44,383
an intervention in your case

380
00:14:44,717 --> 00:14:46,318
would be too risky.

381
00:14:50,122 --> 00:14:52,124
Don't worry. This is a major hospital.

382
00:14:53,192 --> 00:14:54,960
Their Heart Center is famous.

383
00:14:55,194 --> 00:14:56,228
They'll definitely cure you.

384
00:14:57,997 --> 00:14:58,664
Didn't they say

385
00:14:59,164 --> 00:15:00,633
Director Lin in Cardiac Surgery

386
00:15:00,666 --> 00:15:01,600
was the most skilled?

387
00:15:02,968 --> 00:15:04,003
I don't think so.

388
00:15:04,603 --> 00:15:05,571
He's so young,

389
00:15:05,804 --> 00:15:06,605
and his attitude is terrible.

390
00:15:07,306 --> 00:15:08,274
I don't trust him.

391
00:15:08,607 --> 00:15:10,042
Director Luo is different.

392
00:15:10,509 --> 00:15:12,244
He clearly has experience,

393
00:15:12,511 --> 00:15:13,345
and he's kind.

394
00:15:14,213 --> 00:15:15,014
Don't worry.

395
00:15:15,214 --> 00:15:16,649
He'll definitely cure you.

396
00:15:19,285 --> 00:15:20,853
The bankbook and cards

397
00:15:21,954 --> 00:15:22,655
are in the desk,

398
00:15:22,688 --> 00:15:24,023
bottom drawer.

399
00:15:24,523 --> 00:15:25,991
The PIN is your birthday.

400
00:15:27,826 --> 00:15:28,761
There are also

401
00:15:29,228 --> 00:15:30,229
two insurance policies.

402
00:15:30,796 --> 00:15:31,997
The contracts should be with the property deed

403
00:15:32,064 --> 00:15:33,432
in the wardrobe drawer.

404
00:15:34,133 --> 00:15:35,134
Don't forget.

405
00:15:35,267 --> 00:15:36,769
Here you go again.

406
00:15:37,670 --> 00:15:38,904
I've told you eight hundred times.

407
00:15:38,971 --> 00:15:40,239
I don't want to hear this.

408
00:15:42,308 --> 00:15:43,809
They're opening your chest.

409
00:15:45,110 --> 00:15:46,612
The incision is so long.

410
00:15:47,513 --> 00:15:48,547
What if...

411
00:15:48,914 --> 00:15:49,915
There is no what-if.

412
00:15:50,482 --> 00:15:52,117
All you say is bad luck.

413
00:15:52,651 --> 00:15:53,752
Director Luo said

414
00:15:53,852 --> 00:15:55,654
he's very confident in the surgery.

415
00:15:57,122 --> 00:15:57,690
Eat.

416
00:16:05,197 --> 00:16:06,031
Make the call.

417
00:16:07,733 --> 00:16:09,234
Call him.

418
00:16:10,169 --> 00:16:11,770
He still doesn't know you're having surgery.

419
00:16:13,072 --> 00:16:13,706
I won't.

420
00:16:14,974 --> 00:16:17,009
Call him yourself if you want.

421
00:16:29,855 --> 00:16:30,255
He...

422
00:16:32,191 --> 00:16:33,759
He blocked both of us

423
00:16:33,826 --> 00:16:34,994
a long time ago.

424
00:16:39,732 --> 00:16:40,399
That's true.

425
00:16:43,736 --> 00:16:45,237
Even if we call, he won't come.

426
00:16:51,643 --> 00:16:52,611
What's your relationship to the patient?

427
00:16:52,745 --> 00:16:53,612
I'm his friend.

428
00:16:58,717 --> 00:16:59,852
Ward Seven.

429
00:17:00,486 --> 00:17:01,320
Turn left here.

430
00:17:01,553 --> 00:17:02,087
Thank you.

431
00:17:08,727 --> 00:17:09,361
Sorry.

432
00:17:09,728 --> 00:17:10,929
The number you dialed is busy.

433
00:17:11,397 --> 00:17:12,731
Please try again later.

434
00:17:25,411 --> 00:17:26,011
Sorry.

435
00:17:26,478 --> 00:17:27,546
Could I borrow

436
00:17:27,546 --> 00:17:29,148
your landline to make a call?

437
00:17:29,648 --> 00:17:29,948
Sure.

438
00:17:30,582 --> 00:17:30,883
Here.

439
00:17:31,383 --> 00:17:31,683
Thank you.

440
00:17:31,683 --> 00:17:32,384
Dial nine for an outside line.

441
00:17:32,684 --> 00:17:33,118
Thank you.

442
00:17:45,664 --> 00:17:47,399
Hello, Xiao Peng.

443
00:17:47,566 --> 00:17:48,434
This is Aunt Jiang.

444
00:17:48,934 --> 00:17:50,269
Your father is in the hospital.

445
00:17:50,502 --> 00:17:52,037
His surgery is this Wednesday.

446
00:17:52,504 --> 00:17:54,273
Can you come see him?

447
00:17:55,474 --> 00:17:56,442
That was you calling just now, wasn't it?

448
00:17:57,443 --> 00:17:58,110
I won't go.

449
00:17:58,477 --> 00:17:59,144
Don't call me again.

450
00:17:59,678 --> 00:18:01,113
Don't hang up. Listen.

451
00:18:01,880 --> 00:18:02,948
Your father is really

452
00:18:03,015 --> 00:18:04,049
very ill this time.

453
00:18:04,416 --> 00:18:04,716
He...

454
00:18:05,084 --> 00:18:06,251
He really, really wants

455
00:18:06,485 --> 00:18:07,319
to see you.

456
00:18:07,486 --> 00:18:08,554
Don't tell me that.

457
00:18:09,321 --> 00:18:10,556
When the old man hooked up

458
00:18:10,656 --> 00:18:10,989
with you, his mistress,

459
00:18:10,989 --> 00:18:11,790
and drove my mother to death,

460
00:18:11,790 --> 00:18:12,357
where was he?

461
00:18:12,724 --> 00:18:13,492
I won't see him,

462
00:18:13,792 --> 00:18:14,593
and I won't forgive him.

463
00:18:15,127 --> 00:18:17,196
Xiao Peng, after all these years,

464
00:18:17,396 --> 00:18:18,764
you've truly misunderstood us.

465
00:18:18,964 --> 00:18:19,565
It wasn't you.

466
00:18:35,147 --> 00:18:37,516
When days keep passing,

467
00:18:38,116 --> 00:18:39,351
dragging on,

468
00:18:39,685 --> 00:18:40,519
day after day,

469
00:18:40,786 --> 00:18:41,653
year after year,

470
00:18:42,488 --> 00:18:44,423
they eventually blur together.

471
00:18:45,491 --> 00:18:46,325
Every day

472
00:18:46,492 --> 00:18:48,227
loses its own name.

473
00:18:52,831 --> 00:18:53,665
To me,

474
00:18:54,199 --> 00:18:55,134
only words like yesterday

475
00:18:55,367 --> 00:18:56,768
and tomorrow

476
00:18:57,202 --> 00:18:59,004
still carry any meaning.

477
00:19:06,545 --> 00:19:07,546
I called him.

478
00:19:09,281 --> 00:19:10,582
I used the hospital phone.

479
00:19:11,683 --> 00:19:12,518
I told him

480
00:19:12,684 --> 00:19:13,719
you're having surgery today.

481
00:19:14,586 --> 00:19:16,121
I passed on everything I should.

482
00:19:16,922 --> 00:19:18,090
So just focus on the surgery.

483
00:19:25,430 --> 00:19:27,432
Maybe when you wake up,

484
00:19:27,766 --> 00:19:28,400
he'll be here.

485
00:19:30,969 --> 00:19:32,271
He won't come.

486
00:19:34,673 --> 00:19:35,574
Forget it.

487
00:19:38,110 --> 00:19:39,344
At the end of my life,

488
00:19:39,745 --> 00:19:40,646
I guess

489
00:19:41,079 --> 00:19:42,881
my bond with my son was simply too weak.

490
00:19:43,115 --> 00:19:44,316
What do you mean, at the end?

491
00:19:44,516 --> 00:19:45,584
Stop imagining things.

492
00:19:48,387 --> 00:19:50,989
If this time I

493
00:19:52,224 --> 00:19:53,592
really don't wake up...

494
00:19:53,792 --> 00:19:54,793
Don't talk nonsense.

495
00:19:55,928 --> 00:19:56,328
You...

496
00:19:59,431 --> 00:20:00,132
You must...

497
00:20:01,567 --> 00:20:02,467
In this life,

498
00:20:04,036 --> 00:20:05,971
I've owed you too much

499
00:20:07,272 --> 00:20:09,374
and made you suffer too many wrongs.

500
00:20:17,649 --> 00:20:18,684
At least you know.

501
00:20:22,054 --> 00:20:22,588
Since you know,

502
00:20:23,088 --> 00:20:24,389
then get through the surgery.

503
00:20:25,524 --> 00:20:26,391
After discharge,

504
00:20:26,792 --> 00:20:27,993
you can make it up to me properly.

505
00:20:31,863 --> 00:20:33,732
Look at you, like a child.

506
00:20:33,799 --> 00:20:34,666
Don't cry.

507
00:20:37,569 --> 00:20:38,203
Bed 19,

508
00:20:38,804 --> 00:20:39,771
it's time for the operating room.

509
00:20:51,250 --> 00:20:52,884
Let's cover you up.

510
00:20:57,956 --> 00:20:58,490
It's okay.

511
00:21:04,363 --> 00:21:05,030
Don't worry.

512
00:21:12,070 --> 00:21:13,472
The coronary disease is extremely severe.

513
00:21:15,641 --> 00:21:17,342
This is a typical diabetic patient

514
00:21:17,476 --> 00:21:19,211
with diffuse coronary disease.

515
00:21:20,212 --> 00:21:21,113
With Director Luo's excellent

516
00:21:21,146 --> 00:21:21,880
surgical technique,

517
00:21:22,114 --> 00:21:22,881
no vessel is too difficult.

518
00:21:22,914 --> 00:21:23,749
No problem at all.

519
00:21:26,318 --> 00:21:27,286
The LAD

520
00:21:27,319 --> 00:21:29,154
shows diffuse cord-like changes.

521
00:21:29,721 --> 00:21:30,389
There's almost nowhere

522
00:21:30,455 --> 00:21:31,556
suitable for an anastomosis.

523
00:21:32,290 --> 00:21:33,392
We'll need an endarterectomy.

524
00:21:33,925 --> 00:21:34,393
Coronary knife.

525
00:21:37,896 --> 00:21:38,196
Irrigation.

526
00:21:44,670 --> 00:21:45,070
Dissection ruler.

527
00:21:47,673 --> 00:21:48,173
Irrigation.

528
00:21:57,549 --> 00:21:58,684
The calcified intima tore.

529
00:21:59,284 --> 00:22:00,385
It didn't come out intact.

530
00:22:02,320 --> 00:22:02,888
Leave it.

531
00:22:03,889 --> 00:22:04,489
Prepare the graft.

532
00:22:13,932 --> 00:22:14,733
Xiao Nan, irrigate.

533
00:22:26,912 --> 00:22:27,479
Grafting complete.

534
00:22:28,613 --> 00:22:29,081
Measure the flow.

535
00:22:37,689 --> 00:22:38,824
Why is it so low?

536
00:22:42,527 --> 00:22:43,195
The patient's ECG

537
00:22:43,195 --> 00:22:44,529
shows ST-segment changes.

538
00:22:44,863 --> 00:22:45,564
Frequent PVCs.

539
00:22:46,965 --> 00:22:47,999
No, ventricular fibrillation. Treat it now.

540
00:22:52,104 --> 00:22:53,305
Connect cardiopulmonary bypass. Hurry.

541
00:22:56,875 --> 00:22:57,743
Prepare priming and de-airing.

542
00:23:06,685 --> 00:23:07,352
Charged.

543
00:23:07,886 --> 00:23:08,186
Shock.

544
00:23:08,487 --> 00:23:08,787
Shock.

545
00:23:14,826 --> 00:23:15,527
Full-flow support.

546
00:23:19,331 --> 00:23:19,865
No.

547
00:23:20,599 --> 00:23:21,733
Still frequent PVCs.

548
00:23:22,334 --> 00:23:23,535
It has to be the graft.

549
00:23:24,436 --> 00:23:24,903
Director Luo.

550
00:23:25,003 --> 00:23:26,271
Should we redo it?

551
00:23:27,472 --> 00:23:28,206
How can we redo it?

552
00:23:28,507 --> 00:23:29,508
The vessel quality is terrible,

553
00:23:29,708 --> 00:23:30,842
and the endarterectomy was incomplete.

554
00:23:30,976 --> 00:23:31,743
Even if you redo it twice,

555
00:23:31,743 --> 00:23:32,744
won't it end up the same?

556
00:23:38,116 --> 00:23:39,484
We definitely can't leave it like this.

557
00:23:39,651 --> 00:23:40,285
It's obvious

558
00:23:40,318 --> 00:23:41,486
the anastomosis is the problem.

559
00:23:46,591 --> 00:23:47,125
Director Luo,

560
00:23:48,026 --> 00:23:48,760
in this situation,

561
00:23:48,827 --> 00:23:50,228
if we don't redo it,

562
00:23:50,695 --> 00:23:51,463
we'll never get him off bypass.

563
00:23:57,269 --> 00:23:57,936
Director Luo.

564
00:23:58,103 --> 00:23:58,770
Maybe

565
00:23:59,404 --> 00:24:01,039
ask Director Sheng to come look.

566
00:24:07,312 --> 00:24:08,146
Go find out

567
00:24:08,413 --> 00:24:09,114
whether Director Lin is here.

568
00:24:09,948 --> 00:24:10,315
Okay.

569
00:24:17,088 --> 00:24:17,556
Director Lin.

570
00:24:18,723 --> 00:24:19,191
Please wait.

571
00:24:19,825 --> 00:24:20,392
Director Lin,

572
00:24:20,992 --> 00:24:22,360
all three coronary arteries

573
00:24:22,394 --> 00:24:23,361
are severely diseased.

574
00:24:24,229 --> 00:24:24,563
Excuse me.

575
00:24:24,563 --> 00:24:25,263
The LAD is chronically occluded,

576
00:24:25,530 --> 00:24:26,565
with collateral supply from the right coronary artery.

577
00:24:26,731 --> 00:24:27,666
The entire vessel

578
00:24:27,766 --> 00:24:29,034
has diffuse disease,

579
00:24:29,167 --> 00:24:29,835
so I couldn't find

580
00:24:29,935 --> 00:24:30,802
a suitable grafting site.

581
00:24:30,969 --> 00:24:31,837
I performed an endarterectomy,

582
00:24:31,970 --> 00:24:33,104
but it wasn't complete.

583
00:24:33,104 --> 00:24:33,705
All right. Stop.

584
00:24:33,772 --> 00:24:34,239
I'm here now.

585
00:24:51,256 --> 00:24:51,756
Director Lin.

586
00:24:58,396 --> 00:24:59,064
How long on bypass?

587
00:24:59,197 --> 00:25:00,532
Thirty minutes.

588
00:25:05,470 --> 00:25:06,037
This won't work.

589
00:25:06,972 --> 00:25:08,240
The graft has no flow at all.

590
00:25:16,681 --> 00:25:17,883
The intima is completely disrupted.

591
00:25:18,917 --> 00:25:20,252
Collateral circulation can't get through.

592
00:25:21,253 --> 00:25:21,720
Why didn't you

593
00:25:21,720 --> 00:25:23,255
separate the calcified intima completely?

594
00:25:24,689 --> 00:25:25,790
It's not that I refused.

595
00:25:26,124 --> 00:25:27,125
He has diffuse disease

596
00:25:27,158 --> 00:25:28,193
throughout the vessel.

597
00:25:28,793 --> 00:25:30,762
A complete endarterectomy

598
00:25:30,996 --> 00:25:31,997
would take forever.

599
00:25:32,130 --> 00:25:33,031
It wasn't realistic.

600
00:25:35,066 --> 00:25:35,800
However long it takes, we still have to do it.

601
00:25:37,936 --> 00:25:38,803
Extend the coronary incision.

602
00:25:40,505 --> 00:25:41,439
If we extend it further,

603
00:25:41,573 --> 00:25:42,440
how can we anastomose it?

604
00:25:43,308 --> 00:25:44,910
The vessel is only one millimeter wide.

605
00:25:45,110 --> 00:25:45,911
It's soft and slippery.

606
00:25:46,244 --> 00:25:47,879
It's like carving on a sesame seed.

607
00:25:48,113 --> 00:25:49,214
It can't bleed,

608
00:25:49,514 --> 00:25:50,248
and it still has to stay patent.

609
00:25:50,415 --> 00:25:51,216
It's too difficult.

610
00:26:04,763 --> 00:26:05,764
Saphenous vein patch.

611
00:26:09,234 --> 00:26:10,135
Can we really do that?

612
00:26:11,036 --> 00:26:11,703
What other choice is there?

613
00:26:11,803 --> 00:26:12,971
Suture it, stitch by stitch.

614
00:26:26,318 --> 00:26:26,651
Scissors.

615
00:26:40,632 --> 00:26:40,932
Cut.

616
00:26:43,368 --> 00:26:43,969
Measure the flow.

617
00:26:55,480 --> 00:26:55,947
We have flow.

618
00:27:00,652 --> 00:27:01,286
Let's continue.

619
00:27:03,054 --> 00:27:03,655
Give it to me.

620
00:27:14,265 --> 00:27:14,733
Director Lin,

621
00:27:15,233 --> 00:27:16,134
those hands of yours

622
00:27:16,401 --> 00:27:17,869
were born for surgery.

623
00:27:18,436 --> 00:27:18,803
Seriously.

624
00:27:19,070 --> 00:27:19,838
You have to respect it.

625
00:27:21,573 --> 00:27:22,507
Thank you. Thank you.

626
00:27:23,908 --> 00:27:25,043
His cardiac function is poor.

627
00:27:25,110 --> 00:27:26,111
Watch him closely after surgery.

628
00:27:26,811 --> 00:27:27,078
All right.

629
00:27:27,879 --> 00:27:28,313
Director Lin,

630
00:27:30,148 --> 00:27:31,783
a minor operation turned into a major one.

631
00:27:32,517 --> 00:27:33,084
Exactly.

632
00:27:33,385 --> 00:27:33,918
He'll probably need

633
00:27:33,918 --> 00:27:34,252
to stay in the ICU

634
00:27:34,252 --> 00:27:35,186
for some time.

635
00:27:35,987 --> 00:27:36,788
He'll likely require

636
00:27:36,855 --> 00:27:37,389
prolonged ventilatory support too.

637
00:27:37,589 --> 00:27:37,922
Okay.

638
00:27:39,491 --> 00:27:41,126
Closely monitor his circulation,

639
00:27:41,159 --> 00:27:41,593
urine output,

640
00:27:41,626 --> 00:27:42,994
mental status, and everything else.

641
00:27:44,195 --> 00:27:44,929
Yes, Professor Fang.

642
00:27:57,509 --> 00:27:57,809
How about this?

643
00:27:58,176 --> 00:27:59,110
Go see

644
00:27:59,144 --> 00:28:00,345
Director Zhou Xiaofeng in Cardiology

645
00:28:00,478 --> 00:28:01,279
and ask his opinion.

646
00:28:01,513 --> 00:28:02,280
I'll give him a heads-up.

647
00:28:02,614 --> 00:28:02,947
All right?

648
00:28:12,123 --> 00:28:12,757
Hello, Director Ding.

649
00:28:13,391 --> 00:28:13,758
Director Lin.

650
00:28:13,992 --> 00:28:14,559
We have a CABG patient here.

651
00:28:14,592 --> 00:28:15,293
The operation itself went smoothly,

652
00:28:15,427 --> 00:28:16,694
but something still feels wrong.

653
00:28:16,761 --> 00:28:18,129
What's wrong, Director Lin?

654
00:28:24,502 --> 00:28:25,370
Nothing.

655
00:28:27,605 --> 00:28:28,039
I'll go, then.

656
00:28:31,543 --> 00:28:32,444
My flight to Xiamen is at ten tonight.

657
00:28:32,677 --> 00:28:33,912
That late?

658
00:28:34,479 --> 00:28:35,113
I have surgery tomorrow afternoon.

659
00:28:35,513 --> 00:28:36,414
I'm worried a morning flight may be delayed.

660
00:28:36,514 --> 00:28:37,582
All right. Safe travels.

661
00:28:38,049 --> 00:28:39,484
He's still not out of danger.

662
00:28:47,025 --> 00:28:48,593
His cardiopulmonary function was poor before surgery.

663
00:28:48,727 --> 00:28:50,395
On top of that,

664
00:28:50,528 --> 00:28:52,163
he suffered the surgical stress

665
00:28:52,330 --> 00:28:53,431
and a perioperative myocardial infarction.

666
00:28:53,765 --> 00:28:55,200
He still needs high-dose

667
00:28:55,266 --> 00:28:56,367
vasoactive drugs.

668
00:28:56,968 --> 00:28:58,636
There is also significant pulmonary exudation,

669
00:28:58,870 --> 00:28:59,704
so he still requires

670
00:28:59,838 --> 00:29:01,039
continued ventilator support.

671
00:29:02,841 --> 00:29:03,975
How did this happen?

672
00:29:04,509 --> 00:29:06,244
If we'd known, we wouldn't have done surgery.

673
00:29:06,678 --> 00:29:07,045
Then...

674
00:29:07,512 --> 00:29:08,279
Mr. Peng...

675
00:29:08,646 --> 00:29:09,547
Will he be all right?

676
00:29:10,648 --> 00:29:12,117
We'll monitor him closely.

677
00:29:12,550 --> 00:29:13,518
For the next two days,

678
00:29:13,518 --> 00:29:14,719
please don't leave the hospital.

679
00:29:15,053 --> 00:29:16,087
If anything changes,

680
00:29:16,321 --> 00:29:17,388
I'll contact you immediately.

681
00:29:17,889 --> 00:29:18,389
I won't leave.

682
00:29:18,690 --> 00:29:19,591
I'll stay here the whole time.

683
00:29:19,691 --> 00:29:20,492
I won't go anywhere.

684
00:29:20,925 --> 00:29:21,359
All right.

685
00:29:37,408 --> 00:29:38,443
Is this the patient's family?

686
00:29:38,610 --> 00:29:38,877
Yes.

687
00:29:39,144 --> 00:29:40,445
The family of Peng Mao

688
00:29:40,845 --> 00:29:42,147
called the public service hotline

689
00:29:42,147 --> 00:29:43,114
to complain about our hospital.

690
00:29:43,314 --> 00:29:44,549
They believe the surgery was mishandled

691
00:29:45,083 --> 00:29:46,050
and want to hold us responsible.

692
00:29:46,751 --> 00:29:48,186
The patient is still in our ICU,

693
00:29:48,686 --> 00:29:49,754
and they've already complained?

694
00:29:50,321 --> 00:29:51,556
In any case, the family believes

695
00:29:51,589 --> 00:29:52,957
the surgery shouldn't have ended this way.

696
00:29:54,125 --> 00:29:55,093
You mean

697
00:29:55,293 --> 00:29:56,194
the patient underwent open-heart surgery

698
00:29:56,194 --> 00:29:57,328
in Cardiac Surgery,

699
00:29:57,695 --> 00:29:58,797
but they're complaining

700
00:29:58,797 --> 00:29:59,664
about Cardiology?

701
00:30:01,666 --> 00:30:02,800
More precisely,

702
00:30:03,201 --> 00:30:04,669
both Cardiac Surgery and Cardiology

703
00:30:04,836 --> 00:30:05,637
were named in the complaint.

704
00:30:07,639 --> 00:30:08,273
Why?

705
00:30:10,508 --> 00:30:11,609
The family's exact words were:

706
00:30:11,943 --> 00:30:13,478
"My husband was seriously ill.

707
00:30:13,845 --> 00:30:15,613
We came to Dongli Hospital's

708
00:30:15,747 --> 00:30:16,614
Heart Center because of its reputation,

709
00:30:16,848 --> 00:30:18,750
but Cardiac Surgery and Cardiology

710
00:30:18,883 --> 00:30:21,452
kept passing us back and forth,"

711
00:30:21,653 --> 00:30:22,453
"like kicking a ball."

712
00:30:22,654 --> 00:30:24,189
We weren't the ones kicking them around.

713
00:30:24,823 --> 00:30:26,324
He had such severe triple-vessel disease.

714
00:30:26,391 --> 00:30:27,392
We admitted him in good faith

715
00:30:27,559 --> 00:30:28,526
and even operated.

716
00:30:28,760 --> 00:30:30,028
Now somehow we're the ones at fault.

717
00:30:30,762 --> 00:30:31,496
Families

718
00:30:31,729 --> 00:30:33,031
ultimately focus on outcomes.

719
00:30:33,531 --> 00:30:34,933
If the elderly man recovered,

720
00:30:35,066 --> 00:30:36,467
everyone would be happy.

721
00:30:36,668 --> 00:30:37,735
Once the surgical result

722
00:30:37,802 --> 00:30:38,770
falls short of expectations,

723
00:30:39,871 --> 00:30:41,606
the family is bound to have concerns.

724
00:30:42,006 --> 00:30:43,374
What does the family want now?

725
00:30:44,008 --> 00:30:45,276
They only want the entire process clarified

726
00:30:45,476 --> 00:30:46,544
and justice for themselves.

727
00:30:46,845 --> 00:30:47,846
President Wang

728
00:30:47,912 --> 00:30:48,846
is taking this very seriously.

729
00:30:48,947 --> 00:30:49,514
So he asked

730
00:30:49,614 --> 00:30:50,615
the Medical Affairs Office to lead,

731
00:30:50,915 --> 00:30:51,749
and wants everyone

732
00:30:51,883 --> 00:30:52,851
to sit down and discuss it.

733
00:30:56,087 --> 00:30:57,488
The patient's lung function was already poor,

734
00:30:57,689 --> 00:30:58,590
and his cardiac function

735
00:30:58,623 --> 00:30:59,557
has still not recovered.

736
00:30:59,724 --> 00:31:00,758
It's been five days after surgery,

737
00:31:00,792 --> 00:31:02,293
and he still can't be weaned from the ventilator.

738
00:31:06,798 --> 00:31:07,365
Well...

739
00:31:07,665 --> 00:31:09,634
His coronary occlusions were severe,

740
00:31:10,001 --> 00:31:11,236
and his own vessel quality

741
00:31:11,269 --> 00:31:12,036
was poor.

742
00:31:12,270 --> 00:31:14,205
The anastomoses were indeed very difficult.

743
00:31:14,505 --> 00:31:15,073
Later,

744
00:31:15,673 --> 00:31:16,474
fortunately Director Lin

745
00:31:17,208 --> 00:31:18,176
took over.

746
00:31:18,409 --> 00:31:19,711
After that,

747
00:31:19,744 --> 00:31:21,112
I believe the surgery was very successful.

748
00:31:21,946 --> 00:31:23,281
Then why did the family

749
00:31:23,481 --> 00:31:24,849
say your two departments

750
00:31:25,516 --> 00:31:27,085
were passing them back and forth?

751
00:31:33,925 --> 00:31:35,393
The patient's family told me

752
00:31:35,560 --> 00:31:36,494
they first went to

753
00:31:36,527 --> 00:31:37,495
Cardiology's clinic.

754
00:31:37,895 --> 00:31:39,264
But Cardiology told them

755
00:31:39,430 --> 00:31:40,932
the intervention was too risky,

756
00:31:41,032 --> 00:31:42,367
so they should see Cardiac Surgery.

757
00:31:43,401 --> 00:31:44,202
Strictly speaking,

758
00:31:44,669 --> 00:31:46,004
they never registered with Cardiology.

759
00:31:46,838 --> 00:31:48,006
After my clinic ended,

760
00:31:48,172 --> 00:31:49,574
they stopped me in the corridor.

761
00:31:49,674 --> 00:31:50,608
Director Zhou,

762
00:31:53,077 --> 00:31:54,445
I saw how difficult things were for them,

763
00:31:54,512 --> 00:31:55,413
so I reviewed the case.

764
00:31:55,880 --> 00:31:57,081
They had undergone angiography

765
00:31:57,148 --> 00:31:57,782
at a lower-level hospital.

766
00:31:57,949 --> 00:31:59,284
The coronary occlusion was indeed severe,

767
00:31:59,717 --> 00:32:01,252
and most importantly, heavily calcified.

768
00:32:01,319 --> 00:32:02,320
The intervention

769
00:32:02,353 --> 00:32:03,054
would have been extremely difficult.

770
00:32:03,288 --> 00:32:04,656
So I recommended Cardiac Surgery.

771
00:32:04,923 --> 00:32:06,591
Yes. I was there.

772
00:32:06,891 --> 00:32:07,992
Director Zhou was only trying to help.

773
00:32:08,593 --> 00:32:09,727
And if we're talking about who they saw first,

774
00:32:09,794 --> 00:32:10,728
I seem to remember

775
00:32:10,795 --> 00:32:11,763
the patient first went

776
00:32:11,796 --> 00:32:12,964
to Director Lin's clinic.

777
00:32:15,800 --> 00:32:16,134
Yes.

778
00:32:16,401 --> 00:32:17,735
My clinic was almost over that day,

779
00:32:17,735 --> 00:32:19,037
and I added him at the last minute.

780
00:32:19,570 --> 00:32:20,905
He was over seventy,

781
00:32:21,205 --> 00:32:22,640
with poor baseline health,

782
00:32:22,874 --> 00:32:24,309
chronic bronchitis and emphysema.

783
00:32:24,475 --> 00:32:25,076
So I determined

784
00:32:25,109 --> 00:32:26,210
he wasn't a surgical candidate

785
00:32:26,311 --> 00:32:27,512
and sent him to Director Zhou.

786
00:32:28,613 --> 00:32:29,247
But

787
00:32:29,447 --> 00:32:31,215
the family's complaint clearly states

788
00:32:31,916 --> 00:32:33,117
that you personally promised

789
00:32:33,584 --> 00:32:34,786
to call Director Zhou,

790
00:32:34,786 --> 00:32:36,120
but afterward you did not.

791
00:32:36,187 --> 00:32:37,588
Yes. I forgot.

792
00:32:44,529 --> 00:32:45,997
But judging by the outcome,

793
00:32:47,031 --> 00:32:48,366
it made little difference.

794
00:32:48,566 --> 00:32:49,734
Yes.

795
00:32:51,636 --> 00:32:52,036
The outcome was the same.

796
00:32:52,704 --> 00:32:54,405
The family found me,

797
00:32:54,839 --> 00:32:56,240
and I clearly explained

798
00:32:56,574 --> 00:32:58,042
the risks and benefits of intervention.

799
00:32:58,076 --> 00:32:59,043
After hearing that,

800
00:32:59,344 --> 00:33:00,611
After hearing everything,

801
00:33:00,845 --> 00:33:01,612
they probably still decided

802
00:33:01,612 --> 00:33:02,613
to undergo cardiac surgery.

803
00:33:02,947 --> 00:33:03,514
Director Zhou,

804
00:33:04,515 --> 00:33:05,717
was that patient's choice

805
00:33:05,883 --> 00:33:06,918
truly voluntary?

806
00:33:07,652 --> 00:33:08,786
Peng Mao's wife told me

807
00:33:08,886 --> 00:33:10,254
your department said

808
00:33:10,288 --> 00:33:11,255
there were no beds,

809
00:33:11,289 --> 00:33:11,789
so you drove him

810
00:33:11,823 --> 00:33:12,790
to Cardiac Surgery.

811
00:33:15,026 --> 00:33:16,160
I never said that.

812
00:33:16,527 --> 00:33:16,794
Fine.

813
00:33:17,562 --> 00:33:18,596
The moment she left,

814
00:33:18,629 --> 00:33:19,163
your department

815
00:33:19,163 --> 00:33:19,998
admitted another patient.

816
00:33:19,998 --> 00:33:20,531
Isn't that true?

817
00:33:21,065 --> 00:33:22,767
Yes.

818
00:33:23,334 --> 00:33:25,069
I heard you even used a lithotripsy balloon.

819
00:33:25,303 --> 00:33:26,170
So your admission standard

820
00:33:26,437 --> 00:33:27,238
isn't first come, first served?

821
00:33:27,238 --> 00:33:28,039
What does first come, first served

822
00:33:28,673 --> 00:33:29,974
have to do with this?

823
00:33:30,074 --> 00:33:31,542
Mr. Peng and his wife

824
00:33:32,009 --> 00:33:33,111
were still hesitating over treatment.

825
00:33:33,511 --> 00:33:34,278
They hadn't even registered with us.

826
00:33:34,445 --> 00:33:35,146
The later patient

827
00:33:35,279 --> 00:33:36,647
had clear indications for intervention

828
00:33:36,881 --> 00:33:37,749
and a firm decision to proceed.

829
00:33:38,449 --> 00:33:39,183
Why couldn't I admit him?

830
00:33:39,250 --> 00:33:40,084
Was it really because

831
00:33:40,118 --> 00:33:41,252
the patient was still hesitating,

832
00:33:42,587 --> 00:33:43,654
or was there some other reason?

833
00:33:43,788 --> 00:33:44,389
Hard to say.

834
00:33:44,389 --> 00:33:44,956
A little

835
00:33:45,023 --> 00:33:45,723
chronic total occlusion of the LAD

836
00:33:45,757 --> 00:33:47,558
is time-consuming and labor-intensive.

837
00:33:47,558 --> 00:33:48,226
But a lithotripsy balloon plus rotational atherectomy

838
00:33:48,292 --> 00:33:49,327
is a different story.

839
00:33:50,028 --> 00:33:51,162
That has to bring in close to a hundred thousand yuan.

840
00:33:51,229 --> 00:33:51,963
If I were you, I'd do the same.

841
00:33:51,996 --> 00:33:52,563
I understand you, Director Zhou.

842
00:33:52,830 --> 00:33:54,198
Director Luo,

843
00:33:54,599 --> 00:33:55,233
when speaking about a field you don't understand,

844
00:33:55,633 --> 00:33:57,001
I suggest

845
00:33:57,602 --> 00:33:58,302
you be more cautious.

846
00:33:58,770 --> 00:34:00,038
Exactly.

847
00:34:00,204 --> 00:34:01,606
A little LAD chronic total occlusion

848
00:34:02,106 --> 00:34:02,673
was rejected by Director Lin in clinic.

849
00:34:02,907 --> 00:34:03,374
Why?

850
00:34:03,374 --> 00:34:04,175
Because an LAD CTO

851
00:34:04,609 --> 00:34:05,209
isn't worthy of Director Lin.

852
00:34:05,276 --> 00:34:06,077
Now Director Lin

853
00:34:06,110 --> 00:34:06,811
either travels for outside surgery

854
00:34:06,844 --> 00:34:07,645
or occupies

855
00:34:07,912 --> 00:34:08,913
the hybrid operating room.

856
00:34:08,946 --> 00:34:09,514
From now on, will our hospital

857
00:34:09,547 --> 00:34:10,648
only perform

858
00:34:10,815 --> 00:34:11,449
critically ill and complex cases?

859
00:34:11,449 --> 00:34:11,883
What does that have to do

860
00:34:11,916 --> 00:34:12,650
with whether I treat an LAD CTO?

861
00:34:12,917 --> 00:34:14,085
I sent him to Cardiology

862
00:34:14,152 --> 00:34:14,719
to see Director Zhou

863
00:34:14,719 --> 00:34:15,920
because I hoped Director Zhou would assess him

864
00:34:15,920 --> 00:34:16,721
and come back to discuss it with me,

865
00:34:16,788 --> 00:34:17,321
so we could work out

866
00:34:17,321 --> 00:34:18,289
the best treatment plan.

867
00:34:18,456 --> 00:34:18,823
Really?

868
00:34:19,023 --> 00:34:19,891
But without any discussion,

869
00:34:19,891 --> 00:34:20,958
the patient's chest was opened.

870
00:34:21,192 --> 00:34:22,527
Now that something went wrong,

871
00:34:22,593 --> 00:34:23,361
you dump the blame on us.

872
00:34:23,394 --> 00:34:24,395
Is that your logic?

873
00:34:24,595 --> 00:34:25,163
Is that cooperation?

874
00:34:25,196 --> 00:34:26,164
Who helped whom?

875
00:34:26,330 --> 00:34:27,465
Get that straight.

876
00:34:27,532 --> 00:34:28,266
You were the ones who rejected the patient.

877
00:34:28,332 --> 00:34:29,033
When danger arose,

878
00:34:29,033 --> 00:34:30,168
I performed the surgery,

879
00:34:30,368 --> 00:34:31,369
and only then did he leave the table safely.

880
00:34:31,402 --> 00:34:32,370
Yes. I'm not blaming you.

881
00:34:32,370 --> 00:34:33,171
Director Luo is the one shifting blame to us.

882
00:34:38,609 --> 00:34:39,310
Stop talking for a moment.

883
00:34:40,077 --> 00:34:41,045
On this point,

884
00:34:41,479 --> 00:34:41,946
I support Director Lin.

885
00:34:41,946 --> 00:34:42,914
No matter how far back you trace this,

886
00:34:43,047 --> 00:34:43,848
you can't blame him.

887
00:34:44,148 --> 00:34:44,682
Doctors are not

888
00:34:44,715 --> 00:34:45,716
all-knowing, all-powerful gods.

889
00:34:45,950 --> 00:34:46,984
Director Lin only wanted

890
00:34:47,085 --> 00:34:49,053
to find a more suitable treatment for the patient.

891
00:34:49,187 --> 00:34:49,787
So, Director Sheng,

892
00:34:49,887 --> 00:34:51,389
Cardiac Surgery admitted him,

893
00:34:51,489 --> 00:34:52,223
Cardiac Surgery treated him,

894
00:34:52,290 --> 00:34:52,957
and when something went wrong,

895
00:34:52,990 --> 00:34:54,158
Cardiology takes the blame?

896
00:34:54,192 --> 00:34:54,692
Is that the logic?

897
00:34:55,092 --> 00:34:55,927
Why isn't it?

898
00:34:55,927 --> 00:34:56,894
He clearly came to you first,

899
00:34:56,961 --> 00:34:57,428
and you were afraid to take responsibility...

900
00:34:57,562 --> 00:34:58,362
Enough!

901
00:34:58,796 --> 00:34:59,263
What are you arguing about?

902
00:35:00,565 --> 00:35:01,165
Lin Yi.

903
00:35:02,033 --> 00:35:02,967
Where are you going?

904
00:35:03,167 --> 00:35:03,768
I don't want to waste words with him.

905
00:35:07,105 --> 00:35:08,106
Sit down.

906
00:35:10,041 --> 00:35:11,209
Do you have any respect for rules?

907
00:35:11,709 --> 00:35:12,443
What do you think this place is,

908
00:35:12,877 --> 00:35:13,644
a marketplace?

909
00:35:19,484 --> 00:35:20,084
This is a hospital.

910
00:35:21,052 --> 00:35:21,552
President.

911
00:35:21,652 --> 00:35:22,587
The patient

912
00:35:22,854 --> 00:35:23,788
is still not out of danger.

913
00:35:23,855 --> 00:35:25,223
I'm preparing to request

914
00:35:25,690 --> 00:35:27,325
a multidisciplinary consultation,

915
00:35:27,358 --> 00:35:28,192
especially from Respiratory Medicine

916
00:35:29,961 --> 00:35:30,828
and Nephrology.

917
00:35:31,195 --> 00:35:32,029
Dr. Fang is right.

918
00:35:32,263 --> 00:35:33,197
The priority now

919
00:35:33,397 --> 00:35:34,866
is to find a way

920
00:35:35,333 --> 00:35:35,666
to get the patient out of danger.

921
00:35:36,434 --> 00:35:37,602
Xiao Fang,

922
00:35:37,768 --> 00:35:39,170
submit the consultation request

923
00:35:39,470 --> 00:35:41,105
through the system.

924
00:35:41,272 --> 00:35:41,839
I'll speak with

925
00:35:42,707 --> 00:35:43,274
the department heads concerned.

926
00:35:43,374 --> 00:35:44,208
If you need

927
00:35:44,542 --> 00:35:45,076
anything else,

928
00:35:45,443 --> 00:35:46,043
come to me anytime.

929
00:35:47,245 --> 00:35:48,679
Thank you, President.

930
00:35:48,713 --> 00:35:49,614
If there are any changes,

931
00:35:49,647 --> 00:35:50,681
I'll update everyone

932
00:35:52,150 --> 00:35:52,717
immediately.

933
00:35:54,118 --> 00:35:55,086
You two

934
00:35:55,353 --> 00:35:56,554
will each submit a report

935
00:35:56,554 --> 00:35:57,088
clarifying the whole sequence of events.

936
00:35:57,488 --> 00:35:58,556
Explain everything clearly.

937
00:35:58,956 --> 00:35:59,557
Submit it to Medical Affairs

938
00:36:00,725 --> 00:36:01,225
before the end of tomorrow.

939
00:36:01,592 --> 00:36:02,193
Medical Affairs,

940
00:36:14,071 --> 00:36:14,505
Lin Yi.

941
00:36:17,108 --> 00:36:17,575
Director Zhou.

942
00:36:20,077 --> 00:36:21,712
There's something in the department.

943
00:36:22,113 --> 00:36:23,014
Whatever the issue is,

944
00:36:23,447 --> 00:36:24,048
we'll discuss it later.

945
00:36:31,956 --> 00:36:32,823
I'm going back to the ICU.

946
00:36:50,808 --> 00:36:51,909
What was he thinking?

947
00:36:52,810 --> 00:36:53,945
Walking out

948
00:36:54,078 --> 00:36:54,812
in front of everyone

949
00:36:55,646 --> 00:36:57,014
before President Wang had finished speaking.

950
00:36:57,481 --> 00:36:58,716
I couldn't listen anymore.

951
00:36:59,116 --> 00:36:59,951
That man surnamed Wu from Cardiology—

952
00:36:59,951 --> 00:37:00,885
what was he even saying?

953
00:37:01,118 --> 00:37:02,520
It had nothing to do with the facts.

954
00:37:02,920 --> 00:37:03,721
He was venting personal resentment.

955
00:37:04,388 --> 00:37:05,089
Even so,

956
00:37:05,089 --> 00:37:06,023
you didn't need to charge ahead.

957
00:37:06,324 --> 00:37:07,158
I was there.

958
00:37:08,426 --> 00:37:09,927
Fine. Next time I'll follow your lead.

959
00:37:12,263 --> 00:37:13,998
Old Luo has been depressed these days.

960
00:37:14,165 --> 00:37:15,132
His technique

961
00:37:15,132 --> 00:37:15,967
may not be exceptional,

962
00:37:16,233 --> 00:37:17,602
but if he's held accountable

963
00:37:17,668 --> 00:37:18,269
just because one operation

964
00:37:18,436 --> 00:37:19,170
had a poor outcome,

965
00:37:19,437 --> 00:37:20,638
what young doctor

966
00:37:20,671 --> 00:37:21,505
will dare operate in the future?

967
00:37:24,242 --> 00:37:24,976
Actually,

968
00:37:25,009 --> 00:37:26,043
he isn't entirely to blame.

969
00:37:27,044 --> 00:37:28,646
I was Peng Mao's first physician.

970
00:37:29,347 --> 00:37:30,448
I should have followed up.

971
00:37:30,715 --> 00:37:31,849
You've already done your best

972
00:37:31,916 --> 00:37:32,917
to deal with the aftermath.

973
00:37:34,118 --> 00:37:34,852
As for Peng Mao's records,

974
00:37:34,919 --> 00:37:36,153
I reviewed them carefully.

975
00:37:36,687 --> 00:37:37,154
Advanced age,

976
00:37:37,321 --> 00:37:38,522
plus so many underlying diseases—

977
00:37:38,990 --> 00:37:40,558
intervention truly should have been first choice.

978
00:37:40,891 --> 00:37:41,592
Peng Mao was clearly

979
00:37:41,626 --> 00:37:43,194
the kind of patient who'd occupy a bed long-term.

980
00:37:44,195 --> 00:37:45,029
Director Zhou's side

981
00:37:45,162 --> 00:37:46,197
is under performance pressure too.

982
00:37:46,831 --> 00:37:47,832
He was probably in a difficult position.

983
00:37:48,599 --> 00:37:49,266
It's all understandable.

984
00:37:51,602 --> 00:37:52,436
Your favorite.

985
00:37:57,475 --> 00:37:58,509
He has a pulmonary infection,

986
00:37:58,676 --> 00:37:59,877
so we moved him to a private room.

987
00:38:00,111 --> 00:38:01,612
Respiratory Medicine said

988
00:38:01,612 --> 00:38:03,080
for now, apart from continued ventilator support

989
00:38:03,280 --> 00:38:04,649
and intensified airway management,

990
00:38:04,715 --> 00:38:05,716
there isn't a better option.

991
00:38:05,783 --> 00:38:06,350
What's the situation?

992
00:38:10,488 --> 00:38:11,289
What did Nephrology say?

993
00:38:11,722 --> 00:38:12,390
They came too.

994
00:38:12,490 --> 00:38:13,791
They said dialysis isn't needed yet.

995
00:38:14,525 --> 00:38:16,293
If his overall condition improves,

996
00:38:16,327 --> 00:38:17,595
the liver and kidney injury

997
00:38:17,595 --> 00:38:18,562
may ease as well.

998
00:38:19,063 --> 00:38:19,730
So right now,

999
00:38:19,730 --> 00:38:20,531
we can't do anything.

1000
00:38:21,132 --> 00:38:21,732
We can only wait.

1001
00:38:22,366 --> 00:38:23,067
I'll watch him closely.

1002
00:38:24,568 --> 00:38:25,269
His family

1003
00:38:25,369 --> 00:38:26,671
doesn't accept the hospital's findings

1004
00:38:26,837 --> 00:38:28,105
and insists on legal action.

1005
00:38:29,006 --> 00:38:30,307
So you need to be careful too.

1006
00:38:33,611 --> 00:38:34,345
Are you free?

1007
00:38:35,513 --> 00:38:36,147
Let's talk for a while.

1008
00:38:37,948 --> 00:38:38,549
About what?

1009
00:38:48,826 --> 00:38:49,960
What is it? You asked for me.

1010
00:39:08,879 --> 00:39:09,680
Are you okay?

1011
00:39:16,554 --> 00:39:17,254
I'm fine.

1012
00:39:18,189 --> 00:39:18,589
Thank you.

1013
00:39:19,023 --> 00:39:19,557
What about you?

1014
00:39:22,226 --> 00:39:23,761
I feel like something's off with you.

1015
00:39:26,764 --> 00:39:27,465
What's off?

1016
00:39:30,768 --> 00:39:31,802
Zhang Zhen said

1017
00:39:33,437 --> 00:39:34,672
that while you were in Europe,

1018
00:39:36,073 --> 00:39:36,974
you drank alcohol.

1019
00:39:41,912 --> 00:39:42,313
Yes.

1020
00:39:43,848 --> 00:39:44,348
I did.

1021
00:39:45,883 --> 00:39:46,650
What's wrong with that?

1022
00:39:49,487 --> 00:39:50,354
And now,

1023
00:39:51,555 --> 00:39:53,124
you're traveling constantly for surgeries,

1024
00:39:53,758 --> 00:39:54,892
working from dawn to late at night.

1025
00:39:56,761 --> 00:39:57,795
Can your body handle it?

1026
00:39:58,729 --> 00:39:59,797
There's nothing wrong with my body.

1027
00:40:01,532 --> 00:40:02,133
What's wrong with outside surgery?

1028
00:40:02,166 --> 00:40:03,067
It's not a bad thing.

1029
00:40:03,601 --> 00:40:04,602
It's legal and compliant.

1030
00:40:04,969 --> 00:40:05,436
Director Sheng helped me

1031
00:40:05,469 --> 00:40:06,804
complete all the formal procedures.

1032
00:40:07,304 --> 00:40:08,472
If I have time, I go operate.

1033
00:40:08,506 --> 00:40:09,473
I can save more patients.

1034
00:40:09,807 --> 00:40:10,441
What's wrong with that?

1035
00:40:11,876 --> 00:40:12,910
Are you doing it to save patients,

1036
00:40:14,044 --> 00:40:15,212
or for yourself?

1037
00:40:21,185 --> 00:40:21,886
Is there a difference?

1038
00:40:29,593 --> 00:40:30,561
You told me before

1039
00:40:31,962 --> 00:40:32,863
that you'd thought everything through.

1040
00:40:33,664 --> 00:40:34,465
But on your first day back,

1041
00:40:34,532 --> 00:40:35,199
you went straight into surgery.

1042
00:40:35,533 --> 00:40:36,333
You wouldn't rest a few more days.

1043
00:40:36,534 --> 00:40:37,434
I'm better. I'm fine.

1044
00:40:38,803 --> 00:40:40,004
But I don't think you are.

1045
00:40:44,108 --> 00:40:45,042
You're still avoiding it.

1046
00:40:46,076 --> 00:40:47,011
You haven't moved on.

1047
00:40:50,648 --> 00:40:51,348
Then tell me,

1048
00:40:52,850 --> 00:40:54,051
how am I supposed to prove

1049
00:40:54,084 --> 00:40:54,985
I've moved on?

1050
00:40:56,253 --> 00:40:57,688
Do I have to sit at home every day,

1051
00:40:58,756 --> 00:40:59,757
holding my brother's photo

1052
00:40:59,790 --> 00:41:01,091
and crying in Xiaorui's room?

1053
00:41:01,125 --> 00:41:01,926
Would that mean I've moved on?

1054
00:41:02,827 --> 00:41:03,928
Or go to that psychologist you arranged

1055
00:41:03,961 --> 00:41:05,062
and have her tell me again

1056
00:41:05,129 --> 00:41:06,063
that my whole family is dead,

1057
00:41:06,130 --> 00:41:07,331
but I still have to smile

1058
00:41:07,364 --> 00:41:08,532
through the rest of my life?

1059
00:41:08,566 --> 00:41:09,467
Would that count?

1060
00:41:10,434 --> 00:41:11,135
Maybe.

1061
00:41:12,436 --> 00:41:13,704
Maybe that would be better.

1062
00:41:15,606 --> 00:41:17,474
You need time, Lin Yi.

1063
00:41:18,676 --> 00:41:19,543
We suspended

1064
00:41:19,543 --> 00:41:21,111
the elite team's joint clinic

1065
00:41:21,345 --> 00:41:22,546
and surgeries

1066
00:41:22,546 --> 00:41:23,247
to give you time

1067
00:41:23,347 --> 00:41:24,515
to rest

1068
00:41:25,182 --> 00:41:25,883
and recover slowly.

1069
00:41:26,851 --> 00:41:27,751
But what happened?

1070
00:41:28,085 --> 00:41:28,786
The moment Director Sheng spoke,

1071
00:41:28,853 --> 00:41:29,587
you threw yourself into

1072
00:41:29,920 --> 00:41:30,387
valve clinics,

1073
00:41:30,387 --> 00:41:30,921
outside surgeries,

1074
00:41:31,121 --> 00:41:32,389
and TAVR procedures.

1075
00:41:32,423 --> 00:41:33,023
Do you think that helps you?

1076
00:41:33,090 --> 00:41:34,091
Do you think he truly

1077
00:41:34,158 --> 00:41:34,925
cares about your condition?

1078
00:41:34,959 --> 00:41:35,826
I know my own condition

1079
00:41:35,893 --> 00:41:37,294
better than anyone.

1080
00:41:37,695 --> 00:41:39,163
And I know very well

1081
00:41:42,433 --> 00:41:43,367
that Director Sheng has taken care of me.

1082
00:41:43,934 --> 00:41:45,269
The hybrid operating room

1083
00:41:45,569 --> 00:41:46,904
has five surgical days a week,

1084
00:41:47,104 --> 00:41:48,205
and you alone take up two and a half,

1085
00:41:48,873 --> 00:41:49,773
often running overtime.

1086
00:41:49,773 --> 00:41:51,008
People in my department

1087
00:41:51,709 --> 00:41:52,843
are already deeply dissatisfied with you.

1088
00:41:52,843 --> 00:41:53,711
Director Sheng clearly knows,

1089
00:41:53,711 --> 00:41:54,245
but says nothing to you

1090
00:41:54,545 --> 00:41:55,479
and keeps indulging you.

1091
00:41:55,546 --> 00:41:56,313
Do you think he's protecting you,

1092
00:41:56,680 --> 00:41:57,514
or harming you?

1093
00:41:57,548 --> 00:41:59,016
Everyone is yielding to you

1094
00:41:59,049 --> 00:41:59,984
because of me.

1095
00:42:00,050 --> 00:42:00,885
Don't you realize that?

1096
00:42:00,885 --> 00:42:01,552
Then manage your own department.

1097
00:42:01,552 --> 00:42:02,653
What does it have to do with me?

1098
00:42:04,889 --> 00:42:05,956
When you operate, you're saving lives.

1099
00:42:05,990 --> 00:42:07,124
When we operate, we're playing around?

1100
00:42:07,525 --> 00:42:08,492
Besides, how can surgery

1101
00:42:08,525 --> 00:42:09,827
be timed down to the minute?

1102
00:42:10,160 --> 00:42:11,128
If a case is more complicated

1103
00:42:11,161 --> 00:42:11,795
and takes longer,

1104
00:42:11,896 --> 00:42:12,496
isn't that normal?

1105
00:42:12,663 --> 00:42:13,063
What do you want me to do?

1106
00:42:13,130 --> 00:42:13,964
Next time I operate,

1107
00:42:13,964 --> 00:42:14,565
should I watch the clock,

1108
00:42:14,765 --> 00:42:15,633
and when time's up tell the patient,

1109
00:42:15,633 --> 00:42:16,166
"Sorry,

1110
00:42:16,200 --> 00:42:16,734
get off the table for now.

1111
00:42:16,767 --> 00:42:17,568
We'll finish next time"?

1112
00:42:17,735 --> 00:42:18,969
Of course surgical time

1113
00:42:19,036 --> 00:42:20,104
can be roughly estimated.

1114
00:42:20,671 --> 00:42:21,672
If you can't finish,

1115
00:42:21,705 --> 00:42:22,506
you shouldn't schedule so many cases.

1116
00:42:22,640 --> 00:42:24,208
I always finish my operations.

1117
00:42:27,111 --> 00:42:28,112
Since you're so good at estimating,

1118
00:42:28,746 --> 00:42:29,613
please estimate

1119
00:42:29,647 --> 00:42:30,548
my operating time,

1120
00:42:30,681 --> 00:42:31,682
then rearrange

1121
00:42:31,715 --> 00:42:32,550
your own operating schedule.

1122
00:42:32,583 --> 00:42:33,183
Wouldn't that solve it?

1123
00:42:36,287 --> 00:42:36,854
Lin Yi.

1124
00:42:38,122 --> 00:42:39,089
Do you think

1125
00:42:39,924 --> 00:42:41,525
all the concessions I've made to you

1126
00:42:42,159 --> 00:42:43,227
were something you were entitled to?

1127
00:42:46,864 --> 00:42:47,865
Haven't you realized

1128
00:42:48,399 --> 00:42:49,433
that you've already become

1129
00:42:49,466 --> 00:42:50,601
a blade in Director Sheng's hand,

1130
00:42:53,003 --> 00:42:54,405
with its edge
